text: Joseph Henry Millbank (30 September 1919 – February 2002) was an English footballer active in the 1930s and 1940s. He made a total of 39 appearances in The Football League for Queens Park Rangers and Crystal Palace. ==References== Category:1919 births Category:English Football League players Category:Gillingham F.C. players Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players Category:Crystal Palace F.C. players Category:Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. players Category:2002 deaths Category:Association football midfielders Category:English footballers
